    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="556"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2"
                            type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d556fn1">Presumably sent via military channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-03">3 March
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>486. In reply to insistent questioning at a press conference today I stated that
                    Italian merchant ships and war ships are now being used in our war effort by the
                    Allied Mediterranean command and that some of the Italian ships or substitutes
                    therefor from the British and American tonnage will be allocated to the Soviet
                    Navy to assist in their requirements for their war effort.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
